1
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:19,733
My child, I didn't get to
see you, but I'm saying goodbye.

2
00:00:19,867 --> 00:00:21,767
I will never forget you.

3
00:00:21,900 --> 00:00:25,933
And I won't forget
who did this to you.

4
00:00:26,067 --> 00:00:31,533
Eden, from now on,
you can call me mom.

5
00:00:31,667 --> 00:00:32,833
Thank you...

6
00:00:32,967 --> 00:00:34,900
Mom.

7
00:00:35,067 --> 00:00:38,000
What did you do
to Yenyen's baby?

8
00:00:38,133 --> 00:00:40,167
You cursed them, remember?

9
00:00:40,300 --> 00:00:41,467
I knew it!

10
00:00:43,533 --> 00:00:46,367
You haven't changed, Amanda!

11
00:00:51,967 --> 00:00:53,633
I won't let you hurt my mom!

12
00:00:53,767 --> 00:00:55,300
Did you call her mom?

13
00:00:55,433 --> 00:00:58,667
Please, Mom, leave me alone.

14
00:00:58,800 --> 00:01:01,100
Let me go.

15
00:01:01,233 --> 00:01:02,733
So why did she attack
you all of a sudden?

16
00:01:02,867 --> 00:01:04,467
I thought she didn't
hate you anymore.

17
00:01:04,600 --> 00:01:06,800
She's just pretending.

18
00:01:06,933 --> 00:01:08,600
What she showed us during
the party wasn't real.

19
00:01:08,767 --> 00:01:09,700
Party?

20
00:01:09,833 --> 00:01:11,633
Was my mom at the
party the other night?

21
00:01:11,767 --> 00:01:12,967
She gave the party.

22
00:01:13,100 --> 00:01:15,933
She's Lucho Madrigal's wife.

23
00:01:16,067 --> 00:01:18,367
She is Mrs. Madrigal.

24
00:01:18,500 --> 00:01:22,833
So the woman you desperately
want to meet and impress

25
00:01:22,967 --> 00:01:25,233
turns out to be Amanda.

26
00:01:25,367 --> 00:01:28,167
She may be powerful
now that she has money.

27
00:01:28,300 --> 00:01:33,467
But I still have the most
powerful weapon against her.

28
00:01:33,600 --> 00:01:35,900
Rina brainwashed Yenyen.

29
00:01:36,033 --> 00:01:38,267
That's why she is
so upset with me.

30
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:39,233
So that's it?

31
00:01:39,367 --> 00:01:41,033
Are you giving up on Eden?

32
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:44,167
No. I will never give up
on my daughter.

33
00:01:44,300 --> 00:01:47,067
She's the reason
I came back here.

34
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:48,033
Surprise.

35
00:01:49,867 --> 00:01:51,633
I miss you so much.

36
00:01:51,767 --> 00:01:53,167
I missed you too.

37
00:01:53,300 --> 00:01:54,567
Wow!

38
00:01:54,700 --> 00:01:56,733
How sweet!

39
00:01:56,867 --> 00:01:58,700
Sabina, what are
you doing here?

40
00:01:58,833 --> 00:02:01,367
I'm here to invite you
to my birthday party.

41
00:02:01,500 --> 00:02:02,467
You're inviting me too?

42
00:02:02,600 --> 00:02:03,767
Of course.

43
00:02:03,900 --> 00:02:06,667
Congratulations on your
relationship with Red.

44
00:02:06,800 --> 00:02:09,900
So maybe we can put
the past behind us?

45
00:02:10,033 --> 00:02:11,933
Let's be friends, Yenyen.

46
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:15,633
Great! So come to my party.

47
00:02:21,300 --> 00:02:23,233
Sabina's right, Eden.

48
00:02:23,367 --> 00:02:24,200
You have Red.

49
00:02:24,333 --> 00:02:25,367
You are the winner.

50
00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:26,933
You should go to the party.

51
00:02:27,067 --> 00:02:28,700
And flaunt your
relationship with Red.

52
00:02:28,833 --> 00:02:29,667
And your beauty too!

53
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:31,333
Look at you! Perfect!

54
00:02:31,467 --> 00:02:33,600
What are you talking about?

55
00:02:33,733 --> 00:02:34,633
What do I have to flaunt?

56
00:02:34,767 --> 00:02:35,800
My dry hair?

57
00:02:35,933 --> 00:02:37,200
My belly?

58
00:02:38,133 --> 00:02:43,700
I won't mind if my looks
and figure change

59
00:02:43,833 --> 00:02:45,633
as long as
I have my baby with me.

60
00:02:45,767 --> 00:02:47,067
But I lost her.

61
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:48,733
There you go again.

62
00:02:48,900 --> 00:02:51,000
I don't know how to comfort you.

63
00:02:51,133 --> 00:02:52,800
Why don't you just
go back to your mom?

64
00:02:52,933 --> 00:02:54,767
I know she's what you need.

65
00:02:54,900 --> 00:02:57,567
She's back anyway.

66
00:02:57,700 --> 00:02:59,767
Raichu, let's not
talk about my mom.

67
00:02:59,900 --> 00:03:01,933
She has her own life now.

68
00:03:02,067 --> 00:03:06,100
Red and Mommy Rina
is my family now.

69
00:03:06,233 --> 00:03:07,733
I'm glad Red and I
fixed our problems.

70
00:03:07,867 --> 00:03:12,233
Or else I wouldn't
have a place to go.

71
00:03:18,200 --> 00:03:22,600
Yen, if you're not comfortable,
we don't have to go.

72
00:03:22,767 --> 00:03:25,533
But is it okay
if I give her a gift?

73
00:03:28,700 --> 00:03:33,300
Look, I'm just here
to congratulate you.

74
00:03:33,433 --> 00:03:35,300
You and Red are really
meant for each other.

75
00:03:35,433 --> 00:03:40,333
So maybe we can put
the past behind us?

76
00:03:40,467 --> 00:03:42,433
Let's be friends, Yenyen.

77
00:03:46,433 --> 00:03:47,867
Yen...

78
00:03:49,167 --> 00:03:50,400
I hope you understand.

79
00:03:53,067 --> 00:03:55,000
She's been a good
friend to me lately.

80
00:04:02,667 --> 00:04:04,167
Perhaps you're right.

81
00:04:04,300 --> 00:04:08,467
Maybe Sabina just wanted
your friendship back.

82
00:04:09,333 --> 00:04:11,600
Maybe I was just confused.

83
00:04:11,733 --> 00:04:14,933
That's why I thought
she had a motive.

84
00:04:16,500 --> 00:04:17,667
I'm sorry.

85
00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:19,967
No need to apologize.

86
00:04:20,100 --> 00:04:23,133
I understand why
you got mad at me.

87
00:04:23,267 --> 00:04:25,700
We were having problems,
and I was hanging out

88
00:04:25,833 --> 00:04:27,367
with my ex-girlfriend.

89
00:04:27,500 --> 00:04:28,833
I'm sorry too.

90
00:04:31,167 --> 00:04:32,167
But now that our problems
are settled,

91
00:04:32,300 --> 00:04:35,200
you have nothing
to be insecure about.

92
00:04:35,333 --> 00:04:36,467
Really?

93
00:04:36,600 --> 00:04:38,533
Even though I'm sloppy?

94
00:04:39,600 --> 00:04:40,233
Sloppy?

95
00:04:40,367 --> 00:04:42,200
You said you look sloppy?

96
00:04:42,333 --> 00:04:44,600
You look so good to me.

97
00:04:46,533 --> 00:04:47,900
You know what?

98
00:04:48,033 --> 00:04:52,600
I want to show everyone
how lucky I am.

99
00:04:52,733 --> 00:04:53,867
How pretty you are.

100
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:54,833
Okay, fine.

101
00:04:54,967 --> 00:04:56,700
We'll go to that party.

102
00:04:56,833 --> 00:04:58,867
That's what I'm talking about.

103
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:02,867
So I can also tell Sabina
that I accept her offer

104
00:05:03,033 --> 00:05:04,767
of friendship.

105
00:05:06,767 --> 00:05:08,233
You're so nice.

106
00:05:08,367 --> 00:05:10,233
That's why I really love you.

107
00:05:16,133 --> 00:05:17,867
Can you make sure
you're fully stocked

108
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:19,400
for the open bar later?

109
00:05:19,533 --> 00:05:21,767
I want everything
to be in order.

110
00:05:21,900 --> 00:05:23,333
Noted, Miss Sab.

111
00:05:23,467 --> 00:05:25,833
We'll bring out the food
sample we'll serve

112
00:05:25,967 --> 00:05:26,667
at your party later.

113
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:27,700
Kindly wait here.

114
00:05:27,833 --> 00:05:29,467
Okay, thank you so much.

115
00:05:31,700 --> 00:05:35,567
So, I heard you
invited Red and Eden.

116
00:05:37,767 --> 00:05:40,400
I didn't really
want to invite Eden.

117
00:05:40,533 --> 00:05:43,900
I didn't expect them
to fix their problems.

118
00:05:44,033 --> 00:05:46,900
So I had to invite her too.

119
00:05:47,033 --> 00:05:52,300
Sab, if you really love
my friend, just leave them be.

120
00:05:52,433 --> 00:05:55,300
He's happy with Eden now.

121
00:05:55,433 --> 00:05:58,300
You saw how miserable
he was last time.

122
00:06:02,067 --> 00:06:03,067
Yeah!

123
00:06:09,400 --> 00:06:10,900
- Red...
- Sab.

124
00:06:11,033 --> 00:06:14,200
I'm really sorry
about your baby.

125
00:06:14,333 --> 00:06:15,833
That's it?

126
00:06:15,967 --> 00:06:18,667
You won't tell
me I told you so?

127
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:22,733
You won't ask if I regret
choosing Eden over you?

128
00:06:22,867 --> 00:06:25,100
Red, I'm not a monster.

129
00:06:25,233 --> 00:06:27,200
You lost your baby.

130
00:06:27,333 --> 00:06:30,400
And I can't imagine how
painful it is for you.

131
00:06:32,167 --> 00:06:33,700
And besides,

132
00:06:33,833 --> 00:06:37,767
I have already accepted
that you love Eden and not me.

133
00:06:37,900 --> 00:06:39,933
I moved on.

134
00:06:40,067 --> 00:06:41,700
Move on!

135
00:06:41,867 --> 00:06:44,800
You know, that's what
Eden and I argued about.

136
00:06:44,933 --> 00:06:45,833
I know she's hurting,

137
00:06:45,967 --> 00:06:49,133
and I've always been there
for her.

138
00:06:49,267 --> 00:06:52,567
But I'm hurting too.

139
00:06:52,700 --> 00:06:54,767
Who's there for me?

140
00:06:54,900 --> 00:06:56,733
Who's there for me?

141
00:06:57,867 --> 00:06:58,933
You're right.

142
00:06:59,067 --> 00:07:02,000
He was so miserable the
last time that he was here.

143
00:07:03,867 --> 00:07:08,367
That's why I can't let
him stay with that woman.

144
00:07:08,500 --> 00:07:09,767
You know what?

145
00:07:09,900 --> 00:07:12,300
She doesn't deserve him.

146
00:07:12,433 --> 00:07:15,967
She's just making
Red's life miserable.

147
00:07:16,133 --> 00:07:17,567
They just need to realize

148
00:07:17,700 --> 00:07:20,167
they're not meant
for each other.

149
00:07:20,300 --> 00:07:22,500
And I think I can
help with that.

150
00:07:38,867 --> 00:07:41,233
Red, I think I should go home.

151
00:07:41,367 --> 00:07:42,267
I feel shy.

152
00:07:42,400 --> 00:07:44,300
I don't think I'm
dressed for the occasion.

153
00:07:45,367 --> 00:07:47,300
What are you talking about?
You have a pretty dress on.

154
00:07:47,433 --> 00:07:48,967
You just need a
little confidence.

155
00:07:49,133 --> 00:07:51,033
But I don't have that.

156
00:07:51,167 --> 00:07:52,833
Come on. Just follow my lead.

157
00:07:52,967 --> 00:07:53,500
Okay?

158
00:07:53,633 --> 00:07:54,933
You're going to have fun.

159
00:07:57,967 --> 00:07:58,833
Red!

160
00:08:00,533 --> 00:08:01,667
Hey!

161
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:03,067
How are you?

162
00:08:03,200 --> 00:08:06,067
Bro, we've been waiting for you.

163
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:06,900
Hey.
Hi, Eden.

164
00:08:08,033 --> 00:08:09,967
- Hello.
- Come on, let's join them.

165
00:08:10,100 --> 00:08:11,533
I'll go find Sabina.

166
00:08:11,667 --> 00:08:12,933
I want to greet her
a happy birthday.

167
00:08:13,067 --> 00:08:15,700
- Okay, I'll be right there.
- Come on.

168
00:08:15,833 --> 00:08:17,200
Bro.

169
00:08:21,467 --> 00:08:24,767
Well, Eden has a reason
to get insecure with me.

170
00:08:24,900 --> 00:08:26,000
I know Red.

171
00:08:26,133 --> 00:08:29,133
He'll get tired of that
haggard woman soon.

172
00:08:29,267 --> 00:08:30,733
Did you see how
she looks lately?

173
00:08:30,867 --> 00:08:32,000
Oh my god.

174
00:08:32,133 --> 00:08:33,533
Sabina.

175
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:37,267
I knew it.
You still haven't changed.

176
00:08:37,400 --> 00:08:41,200
You really won't stop until you
ruin our relationship.

177
00:08:41,333 --> 00:08:43,733
I'm just telling
the truth, Yenyen.

178
00:08:43,867 --> 00:08:46,733
Did you know how happy Red
was with me the last time

179
00:08:46,867 --> 00:08:48,600
we were together?

180
00:08:48,733 --> 00:08:51,367
The time you lost your baby?

181
00:08:51,500 --> 00:08:53,367
You're pitiful.

182
00:08:53,500 --> 00:08:57,233
You have to make up stories
just to get Red back.

183
00:08:57,400 --> 00:08:58,767
You're desperate.

184
00:08:59,900 --> 00:09:02,300
I'm not making
a story, Yenyen.

185
00:09:02,433 --> 00:09:06,100
In fact, I have a proof.

186
00:09:10,733 --> 00:09:12,067
Wait, wait, wait!

187
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:13,633
Let's take a video!

188
00:09:13,767 --> 00:09:14,533
Hurry!

189
00:09:14,667 --> 00:09:16,133
- To remember this night.
- Come on!

190
00:09:16,267 --> 00:09:18,633
- Come on!
- Put that away!

191
00:09:18,767 --> 00:09:22,167
You know what, I never thought
I'd see you like this again.

192
00:09:22,300 --> 00:09:25,500
It's good to see that you're
still the life of the party!

193
00:09:25,633 --> 00:09:27,200
Yes!

194
00:09:27,333 --> 00:09:32,800
I thought you'd change
after what happened to Eden.

195
00:09:32,967 --> 00:09:34,400
What?

196
00:09:34,533 --> 00:09:35,700
Nothing's changing.

197
00:09:37,333 --> 00:09:40,900
I'm happy now.
Because I'm a free man.

198
00:09:41,033 --> 00:09:43,367
I don't have to change diapers.

199
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:46,667
I don't need to make
baby bottles.

200
00:09:46,800 --> 00:09:48,333
Because my baby's gone.

201
00:09:48,467 --> 00:09:50,233
So what else can I do?

202
00:09:52,133 --> 00:09:53,767
So let's just have fun!

203
00:09:53,900 --> 00:09:55,267
This is the life!

204
00:09:55,400 --> 00:09:57,933
This is the bachelor's life!

205
00:09:58,067 --> 00:09:59,467
It's so nice!

206
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:00,867
This is fun!

207
00:10:01,733 --> 00:10:02,767
See?

208
00:10:03,833 --> 00:10:06,000
He's happy, right?

209
00:10:06,133 --> 00:10:07,500
That's not true.

210
00:10:07,633 --> 00:10:09,167
I'm sorry, Yenyen.

211
00:10:09,300 --> 00:10:11,167
But this is the real Red.

212
00:10:11,300 --> 00:10:14,667
He likes to party
and have fun.

213
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:18,500
That's why he was relieved
when you lost the baby.

214
00:10:18,633 --> 00:10:20,500
Stop it, Sabina!

215
00:10:20,633 --> 00:10:22,700
Oh my god!
Why are you getting mad at me?

216
00:10:22,833 --> 00:10:24,833
I'm just telling you the truth.

217
00:10:25,700 --> 00:10:26,700
You know what?

218
00:10:27,833 --> 00:10:29,400
Why don't you come here?

219
00:10:31,467 --> 00:10:33,100
Come here and look at him.

220
00:10:33,233 --> 00:10:36,000
And tell me that I'm wrong.

221
00:10:36,167 --> 00:10:37,433
Go ahead.

222
00:10:37,567 --> 00:10:38,433
Red!

223
00:10:39,533 --> 00:10:40,300
- Hi!
- Sab!

224
00:10:40,433 --> 00:10:41,467
Happy Birthday!

225
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:43,433
Thank you so much.

226
00:10:43,567 --> 00:10:44,533
Thank you.

227
00:10:45,367 --> 00:10:46,033
Thank you.

228
00:10:47,667 --> 00:10:50,167
Yen, it's okay.

229
00:10:50,300 --> 00:10:51,900
You can drink if you want.

230
00:10:52,033 --> 00:10:53,667
We'll book a ride home.

231
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:55,833
Don't worry about anything.

232
00:10:55,967 --> 00:10:57,300
You seem to be having fun.

233
00:10:58,700 --> 00:10:59,833
Of course.

234
00:10:59,967 --> 00:11:02,400
It's the first time we'll
have a drink together.

235
00:11:02,533 --> 00:11:04,767
I'm so happy because
it's the first time

236
00:11:04,900 --> 00:11:06,933
we'll experience what young
couples usually do.

237
00:11:07,067 --> 00:11:09,967
I'm so excited to
experience that with you.

238
00:11:10,133 --> 00:11:10,967
- Red.
- Why?

239
00:11:11,100 --> 00:11:12,933
Because we don't have
our baby anymore?

240
00:11:13,067 --> 00:11:13,900
Shot?

241
00:11:14,033 --> 00:11:15,733
- Come on, Bro!
- Yen, let's have a shot.

242
00:11:15,867 --> 00:11:16,767
I need to use the restroom.

243
00:11:17,567 --> 00:11:18,667
Okay.

244
00:11:21,233 --> 00:11:23,533
Yeah. What are we drinking?

245
00:11:50,900 --> 00:11:51,667
Let me see.

246
00:11:53,567 --> 00:11:59,967
You know what, I've been
wanting to give you a gift.

247
00:12:00,100 --> 00:12:04,567
I want to thank you...

248
00:12:04,700 --> 00:12:08,400
for looking after Yenyen,

249
00:12:08,533 --> 00:12:10,167
especially when
I wasn't there.

250
00:12:10,300 --> 00:12:14,067
But I can only do it now.

251
00:12:17,800 --> 00:12:21,267
God has given you a lot
of blessings, Amanda.

252
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:24,367
In return for what
you've been through.

253
00:12:27,333 --> 00:12:31,233
So perhaps...

254
00:12:32,267 --> 00:12:35,300
you can put
the past behind you now.

255
00:12:39,267 --> 00:12:42,233
Reconcile with the Ramoses.

256
00:12:46,333 --> 00:12:48,367
So you and Eden can
patch things up.

257
00:12:51,433 --> 00:12:54,500
Did you know why a lot of
people are getting abused?

258
00:12:58,067 --> 00:13:00,533
Because they forget easily.

259
00:13:02,667 --> 00:13:04,900
They're so forgiving.

260
00:13:07,867 --> 00:13:12,267
Even if the people who hurt them
don't regret anything.

261
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:18,200
I can't let that happen.

262
00:13:20,433 --> 00:13:23,867
I won't let Rina abuse me.

263
00:13:29,500 --> 00:13:34,967
And I can't let them
near Eden and me forever.

264
00:13:39,100 --> 00:13:43,333
That's why I will show
Eden how evil they are.

265
00:13:44,800 --> 00:13:52,933
Because once Eden gets hurt,
I'm sure she'll come back to me.

266
00:14:08,900 --> 00:14:10,333
Who are you looking for?

267
00:14:12,033 --> 00:14:13,800
Have you seen Yenyen?

268
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:18,467
She's not here. But I am.

269
00:14:22,900 --> 00:14:25,233
Sab, what are you doing?

270
00:14:25,367 --> 00:14:26,467
Are you drunk?

271
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:28,233
No, I'm not drunk.

272
00:14:28,400 --> 00:14:29,800
In fact, I know what I'm doing.

273
00:14:29,933 --> 00:14:31,467
And I know what I want.

274
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:32,800
And I want you, Red.

275
00:14:32,933 --> 00:14:34,200
Wait!

276
00:14:35,033 --> 00:14:36,867
I thought you'd moved on.

277
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:38,667
Really, Red?

278
00:14:38,800 --> 00:14:41,167
How can I move on when
every time I see you,

279
00:14:41,300 --> 00:14:43,767
you're just perfect.

280
00:14:43,900 --> 00:14:45,033
I want you.

281
00:14:45,167 --> 00:14:47,833
And I want the love
you're giving Yenyen.

282
00:14:47,967 --> 00:14:50,133
Please, just give it to me
just for tonight.

283
00:14:50,267 --> 00:14:50,833
Stop!

284
00:14:50,967 --> 00:14:52,167
Stop, please.

285
00:14:52,300 --> 00:14:54,300
No, listen to me.

286
00:14:54,433 --> 00:14:55,967
Red, you don't have
to stay with Yenyen

287
00:14:56,100 --> 00:14:57,900
if you only pity her.

288
00:14:58,033 --> 00:14:59,233
We can start over.

289
00:14:59,367 --> 00:15:00,967
Your baby's gone.

290
00:15:01,100 --> 00:15:04,333
- You can leave her now.
- Sab, please, stop!

291
00:15:04,500 --> 00:15:07,400
What Eden and I have is real.

292
00:15:07,533 --> 00:15:10,633
I know that because I longed
for no one but her

293
00:15:10,767 --> 00:15:12,667
when we lost our baby.

294
00:15:12,800 --> 00:15:14,667
Sab, I love Yenyen.

295
00:15:14,800 --> 00:15:17,167
And you have to accept that.

296
00:15:19,500 --> 00:15:22,033
Well, you won't find her here,
because she had left.

297
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:25,200
What?

298
00:15:25,333 --> 00:15:26,167
Why?

299
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:27,233
I guess that's for me to know.

300
00:15:27,367 --> 00:15:29,267
And for you to find out.

301
00:15:52,167 --> 00:15:52,833
How did that happen?

302
00:15:54,033 --> 00:15:56,033
We told you to leave!

303
00:15:56,167 --> 00:15:57,567
We gave you a plane ticket!

304
00:15:58,733 --> 00:16:00,867
Lucho, we had some trouble.

305
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:03,000
My wife is in the hospital.

306
00:16:03,133 --> 00:16:05,200
I can't leave her there.

307
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:12,367
Is it true that Zandro
kidnapped Manny?

308
00:16:12,533 --> 00:16:14,433
All I know is that some
people saw him,

309
00:16:14,567 --> 00:16:16,667
but no one wanted
to come forward.

310
00:16:16,800 --> 00:16:20,667
Because they know that Manny
is running an illegal business.

311
00:16:22,100 --> 00:16:25,633
I'm afraid that Zandro
will get me.

312
00:16:25,767 --> 00:16:28,267
What if he hurts my family too?

313
00:16:31,400 --> 00:16:34,033
We both know it can happen.

314
00:16:34,167 --> 00:16:37,000
That's why we want
you to leave the town.

315
00:16:37,133 --> 00:16:38,233
Don't worry.

316
00:16:39,433 --> 00:16:41,767
We'll take care of you.

317
00:16:41,933 --> 00:16:42,567
Thank you.

318
00:16:42,700 --> 00:16:43,933
Thank you, Lucho.

319
00:16:50,967 --> 00:16:52,900
Hey, don't overdo it.

320
00:16:53,033 --> 00:16:55,467
We need him to talk.

321
00:17:00,300 --> 00:17:01,700
Right.

322
00:17:03,300 --> 00:17:05,233
That's what you get.

323
00:17:05,367 --> 00:17:09,033
You mess with the wrong people.

324
00:17:09,167 --> 00:17:11,600
I'm just making a living.

325
00:17:11,733 --> 00:17:14,500
Who bought those
counterfeit money?

326
00:17:14,633 --> 00:17:16,067
Is it Amanda Madrigal?

327
00:17:16,233 --> 00:17:17,200
Answer me!

328
00:17:17,333 --> 00:17:19,500
I don't know who she is!

329
00:17:19,633 --> 00:17:21,767
I'm just selling my products.

330
00:17:21,900 --> 00:17:24,800
I don't know who I sold them to.

331
00:17:47,233 --> 00:17:49,200
Rina's a monster!

332
00:17:49,367 --> 00:17:51,667
Look at what she did to Manny.

333
00:17:52,533 --> 00:17:53,967
Don't worry.

334
00:17:54,100 --> 00:17:55,200
He won't tell her anything.

335
00:17:55,333 --> 00:17:57,867
He'll die before he
tells them anything.

336
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:00,667
I'm not worried
for myself, Lucho.

337
00:18:00,800 --> 00:18:05,367
I'm worried that someone else
might get hurt because of me.

338
00:18:05,500 --> 00:18:07,733
I can't forgive myself
if that happens.

339
00:18:08,633 --> 00:18:13,267
Amanda, you have to prepare
for this.

340
00:18:13,400 --> 00:18:16,733
You've waged war against Rina.

341
00:18:18,100 --> 00:18:21,800
Can we bring Rina down faster?

342
00:18:23,333 --> 00:18:25,467
Before other people get hurt.

343
00:18:25,600 --> 00:18:29,500
She might also hurt
Eden to get back at me.

344
00:18:29,633 --> 00:18:31,867
I want to get my daughter back.

345
00:18:33,500 --> 00:18:35,400
Don't worry.

346
00:18:35,533 --> 00:18:37,833
We have to adjust our plans.

347
00:18:43,100 --> 00:18:44,533
I've been trying to call you,

348
00:18:44,667 --> 00:18:45,833
but you're not answering
your phone.

349
00:18:49,433 --> 00:18:50,667
I didn't see your calls.

350
00:18:50,800 --> 00:18:52,567
I'm sorry.

351
00:18:53,833 --> 00:18:56,300
Where were you off
to with Zandro?

352
00:19:13,333 --> 00:19:17,100
So you want to forget
about our baby?

353
00:19:17,233 --> 00:19:21,300
I will do something to
get all her memories out!

354
00:19:21,433 --> 00:19:24,400
I'll take all of this out!

355
00:19:26,667 --> 00:19:28,800
Mom, Dad.

356
00:19:31,967 --> 00:19:33,667
Have you seen Yenyen?

357
00:19:33,800 --> 00:19:35,967
She just left the party
all of a sudden.

358
00:19:36,100 --> 00:19:38,300
I tried to call her, but...

359
00:19:38,433 --> 00:19:39,933
I saw her earlier.

360
00:19:40,067 --> 00:19:42,100
She probably went to her room.

361
00:19:46,733 --> 00:19:48,367
I'm done!

362
00:19:48,500 --> 00:19:49,533
- That's Eden!
- What is it?

363
00:19:49,667 --> 00:19:50,800
Mom!

364
00:19:50,933 --> 00:19:51,800
That's Yenyen.

365
00:19:51,933 --> 00:19:55,000
- Yen!
- What's going on?

366
00:19:55,133 --> 00:19:56,200
Yen!

367
00:19:59,600 --> 00:20:01,900
- Yen.
- So you want to forget?

368
00:20:02,067 --> 00:20:03,833
Are you happy?

369
00:20:05,100 --> 00:20:06,000
Yen?

370
00:20:09,733 --> 00:20:11,367
Yen!

371
00:20:11,500 --> 00:20:12,800
Yen, open the door!

372
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:15,667
Open the door.
Yen, let's talk.

373
00:20:16,600 --> 00:20:17,267
Yen!

374
00:20:19,633 --> 00:20:20,700
Emma!

375
00:20:20,833 --> 00:20:24,667
Emma, get the key to this room!

376
00:20:24,800 --> 00:20:26,267
Hurry, Emma!

377
00:20:26,400 --> 00:20:28,000
Yen, open the door.

378
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:31,467
Eden, what's going on with you?

379
00:20:31,600 --> 00:20:33,033
Yen, don't hurt yourself.

380
00:20:33,167 --> 00:20:34,100
Open the door.

381
00:20:35,700 --> 00:20:36,400
Mom!

382
00:20:36,533 --> 00:20:37,667
Emma, the key!

383
00:20:48,133 --> 00:20:48,967
Yen!

384
00:20:50,867 --> 00:20:52,567
What's the matter with you?

385
00:20:52,700 --> 00:20:53,700
You!

386
00:20:53,833 --> 00:20:56,067
All of you! You're my problem!

387
00:20:56,200 --> 00:20:58,467
Mom, can you give us a moment?

388
00:20:58,600 --> 00:20:59,533
Go on, please.

389
00:20:59,667 --> 00:21:00,700
Please let us talk in private.

390
00:21:00,833 --> 00:21:01,400
Come on.

391
00:21:01,533 --> 00:21:02,667
Come on, Rina.

392
00:21:02,800 --> 00:21:03,767
Go on.

393
00:21:03,900 --> 00:21:04,733
Come on.

394
00:21:06,667 --> 00:21:07,867
What's the matter?

395
00:21:09,933 --> 00:21:11,933
What is it? Talk to me!

396
00:21:12,067 --> 00:21:14,367
I thought we were okay.

397
00:21:14,500 --> 00:21:16,667
Yen, I've been doing
my very best for us.

398
00:21:16,800 --> 00:21:18,200
I don't deserve this
treatment from you!

399
00:21:18,333 --> 00:21:19,267
Deserve?

400
00:21:19,400 --> 00:21:20,533
You're right!

401
00:21:20,667 --> 00:21:22,767
- This is what you deserve!
- What's going on with you?

402
00:21:22,900 --> 00:21:24,533
What happened?

403
00:21:24,667 --> 00:21:25,933
Go and drink with your friends!

404
00:21:26,067 --> 00:21:26,900
Isn't that what you want?

405
00:21:27,033 --> 00:21:28,167
What's going on?

406
00:21:28,300 --> 00:21:29,133
- Isn't that what you want?
- Where is this coming from?

407
00:21:29,267 --> 00:21:31,067
So you're happy that
we lost our child?

408
00:21:31,200 --> 00:21:32,267
What?

409
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:33,167
- Where is this coming from?
- Oh, so you don't know?

410
00:21:33,300 --> 00:21:35,033
Are you denying it, Red?

411
00:21:35,167 --> 00:21:37,633
I know you're happy
that we lost the baby.

412
00:21:37,767 --> 00:21:40,033
Can you please
stop accusing me?

413
00:21:40,167 --> 00:21:41,000
I'm not making this up!

414
00:21:41,133 --> 00:21:42,167
- Stop it!
- I'm not making things up!

415
00:21:42,333 --> 00:21:44,300
You're giving
a different meaning

416
00:21:44,433 --> 00:21:45,467
to everything I do and say!

417
00:21:45,600 --> 00:21:46,667
What's your problem?

418
00:21:46,800 --> 00:21:47,800
I'm not making things up, Red!

419
00:21:47,933 --> 00:21:48,967
I heard it!

420
00:21:49,100 --> 00:21:52,033
I saw it when you told
your friends you were happy

421
00:21:52,167 --> 00:21:53,900
that we'd lost our baby!

422
00:21:54,033 --> 00:21:57,233
I can't even remember the last
time I was drunk then!

423
00:21:57,367 --> 00:21:58,400
I don't remember anything!

424
00:21:58,533 --> 00:22:02,000
I can't remember a single thing
because I was drunnk!

425
00:22:02,133 --> 00:22:03,233
What's the matter with you?

426
00:22:03,367 --> 00:22:07,100
So you are saying that you never
said that about our baby?

427
00:22:07,233 --> 00:22:08,267
Yen.

428
00:22:12,633 --> 00:22:13,733
Yen, come on.

429
00:22:14,800 --> 00:22:16,133
Get out.

430
00:22:18,100 --> 00:22:20,300
- Let's talk.
- Get out!

431
00:22:20,433 --> 00:22:21,833
- We have to talk.
- I said get out!

432
00:22:21,967 --> 00:22:23,367
Get out!
I'm so tired of this, Red!

433
00:22:23,500 --> 00:22:25,833
- I'm so tired!
- What's the matter with you?

434
00:22:25,967 --> 00:22:27,500
Get out!

435
00:22:27,633 --> 00:22:28,833
Get out!

436
00:22:28,967 --> 00:22:29,867
Yen!

437
00:22:32,233 --> 00:22:33,467
Yen!

438
00:23:07,167 --> 00:23:09,767
I disowned Eden
because of Rina.

439
00:23:09,900 --> 00:23:14,733
What if I really am the
reason she lost her baby?

440
00:23:14,867 --> 00:23:16,767
Don't blame yourself.

441
00:23:16,900 --> 00:23:20,133
If she chose you,
she could have a family.

442
00:23:20,267 --> 00:23:24,300
Thank you for taking me in.

443
00:23:24,467 --> 00:23:26,033
I'm leaving now.

444
00:23:26,167 --> 00:23:28,633
Didn't you check on her before
you went to sleep last night?

445
00:23:28,767 --> 00:23:30,433
We had a big fight last night.

446
00:23:30,567 --> 00:23:32,100
That's why I didn't talk to her.

447
00:23:32,233 --> 00:23:34,067
I thought she needed more time.

448
00:23:34,200 --> 00:23:36,067
You prolonged your fight.
Look at what happened.

449
00:23:36,200 --> 00:23:37,767
Eden left.

450
00:23:37,900 --> 00:23:40,200
She probably went to Amanda.

451
00:23:40,333 --> 00:23:41,400
Yenyen!

452
00:23:41,533 --> 00:23:42,500
Yen, I'm here now!

453
00:23:42,633 --> 00:23:43,800
I thought you were well-off.

454
00:23:43,933 --> 00:23:46,667
Why are you still
have no manners?

455
00:23:46,800 --> 00:23:49,967
Coming over without
notice is bad etiquette.

456
00:23:50,100 --> 00:23:51,633
We're here to get Yenyen.

457
00:23:51,767 --> 00:23:52,900
Where is she?

458
00:23:53,033 --> 00:23:54,333
- Yen!
- She's staying with you,

459
00:23:54,467 --> 00:23:55,500
isn't she?

460
00:23:55,667 --> 00:23:57,800
Why are you looking
for her here?

461
00:23:57,933 --> 00:23:59,433
Is she not here?

462
00:23:59,567 --> 00:24:01,900
She's not here.
What are you talking about?

463
00:24:02,033 --> 00:24:03,900
Is she missing?
